(109, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMTo2MjE1MToy', 2, 0, 1, 'Eryngium yuccifolium Michx.', 'Rattlesnake master', 'Apiaceae (Carrot)', NULL, NULL, '1. Occurs in dry or sandy soils in open woods and prairies (Gleason and Cronquist 1991);', NULL, NULL, 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1. Use of fibers seen in braided work and cloth from the Hopewell and rock-shelter cultures of Ohio. Fibers were usually not treated before use (Whitford 1941);', 'FALSE', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'TRUE', 'TRUE', 'TRUE', 'TRUE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', NULL, 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'na', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-19 22:48:21', '2017-09-19 22:48:21')
(110, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMTo4OTg2NDoy', 2, 0, 1, 'Euonymous atropurpureus Jacq.', 'Wahoo, Burning bush', 'Celastraceae (Staff-tree)', 'mahweeyaahkwi', '1. A plant six to seven feet high (Gatschet ca. 1895); 2. Upright shrub to 2.5 m (Gleason and Cronquist 1991);', '1. Observed growing on the Peoria reservation (Gatschet ca. 1895);', NULL, NULL, 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', '1. UNKNOWN: Dunn lists the word \"mawhaiakwi\" and \"wapak\'kwi\", as the plant called wahoo, or Euonymous atropurpureus (Dunn ca. 1900:5173dw);', NULL, NULL, '1. Popularly called \"wohu\" or \"wahoo\" on the Peoria reservation. Also known as \"panther bush.\" (Gatschet ca. 1895); 2. Wahoo or burning bush. \"The leaves and fruit are reported to possess purgative properties, and at one time the bark of the root was used medicinally but is now occaisonally found employed as a gastric stimulant and cathartic. The powdered bark was used by the Indians for tobacco. The wood was used for arrows by American Indians (Steyermark 1963, information from Fernald and Kinsey 1958 and Hill 1952);', 'FALSE', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', NULL, 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', '-1900', '-1900', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-19 22:48:21', '2017-09-19 22:48:21')
