(147, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMjo2MjAyMToy', 2, 0, 1, 'Marrubium vulgare L.', 'Horehound', 'Lamiaceae (Mint)', NULL, NULL, '1. An introduced species occuring in disturbed places throughout eastern and western Miami lands and the U.S. (Gleason and Cronquist 1991);', NULL, NULL, 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', '1. MEDICINAL: leaves made into cough syrup (Interview with Sharon Prescott, MTO Language Camp, Longhouse, Miami, OK, 6/6/03, collective information from a collecting trip with 3 local Cherokee and 3 Miami women, in Miami); 2. MEDICINAL: tea made by boiling \"spicnert\", horehound, comfrey, cherry bark and \"alicompain\"[spelling may not be accurate] (Mildred Walker\'s papers, given to Myaamia Project 2004);', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FALSE', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', NULL, 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', '2003', '2004', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-19 22:48:22', '2017-09-19 22:48:22')
(148, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwMjo2MzQ3OjI=', 2, 0, 1, 'Mentha piperita L.', 'Peppermint', 'Lamiaceae (Mint)', '(peetihsahki) (also for sweet everlasting)', NULL, '1. Occurs in wet places (Small 1903, Gleason and Cronquist 1991);', NULL, NULL, 'TRUE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', '1. CUSTOMS: added to tobacco with leaves of red cedar (Gatschet ca. 1895); 2. MEDICINAL: tea made from leaves. Not necessarily a medicine, just a drink (Interview with Jim Strack, Tippman 1999); 3. FOOD: candy made from mint. The juice of the plant was cooked down and made into candy (Interview with Jim Strack, Tippman 1999);  4. UNKNOWN: \"pa\'tsakgi, white peppermint, grows wild around the Peoria reservation. It is the Mentha peperita of botany, but the Indians name means \"stink weed\" (Gatschet ca. 1895:1930);', NULL, NULL, '1. Dried leaves and tops of Mentha spicata (same as M. viridis, spearmint) used as an aromatic, stimulant, carminative 000?, and diuretc. M. piperita (peppermint) has the same uses as well as an antispasmodic (Coulter 1932, Published by Eli Lilly & Co.);', 'FALSE', NULL, NULL, '(stink weed, Gat)', NULL, 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'TRUE', 'TRUE', NULL, 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'TRUE', '1895', '1999', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-19 22:48:22', '2017-09-19 22:48:22')
