(187, 'MTUwNTg2MTMwNDo2NDczNjoy', 2, 0, 1, 'Ptelea trifoliata L.', 'Hop-tree, (See Rel. Info.)', 'Rutaceae (Rue)', 'kinoonsaawiaahkwi', NULL, '1. Occurs in rich woods and thickets in eastern and western Miami lands (Gleason and Cronquist 1991);', NULL, NULL, 'FALSE', 'TRUE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', 'FALSE', '1. MEDICINAL: used to treat malaria. \"kinozawiakwi, decoction of, used for malaria\" (Dunn ca. 1900:2705dw); 2. MEDICINAL: the root used to reduce bile and regulate the liver functioning.  \"kinonzawi-axkwi, a medicinal bush growing on the Peoria reservation, six to seven feet high and popularly called wohu, wahoo. The root reduces bile, regulates the system and is good against biliousness [suffering from liver dysfunction--an excessive secretion of bile],\" \"panther bush.\" (Gatschet ca. 1895:745, 756, 755);', NULL, NULL, '1. This tree also known as shrubby treefoil or water ash [although this is the common name for Fraxinus caroliana, a different genus and species] (Dunn circa 1909);', 'FALSE', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-09-19 22:48:24', '2017-09-19 22:48:24')
